# Cursor: Archetype Orchestrator Rules
# Waygate AI Project

## Mandatory Session-Start Sequence

Every session MUST begin with:
1. **MANDATORY: Search open-brain at the START of EVERY task. No exceptions.** Do this BEFORE your first action.
2. Read `docs/planning/CONTEXT_CHECKPOINTS.md`
3. Run: `python ../archetype-orchestrator/engine/discover.py --scan`
4. Verify you are on a feature branch (not main/master/develop)

## Absolute Rules

- NEVER commit directly to main, master, or develop
- NEVER hardcode secrets, API keys, passwords, or tokens
- NEVER use eval() or exec() with user-supplied input
- NEVER call provider SDKs (anthropic, openai) directly — always go through LLMClient
- NEVER remove or weaken DEFAULT_CANARY without updating security/evidence/
- NEVER log or print API key values
- ALWAYS run pre-work-check.sh before starting any task
- ALWAYS run post-work-check.sh before declaring a task done
- ALWAYS run validation before committing: bash ../archetype-orchestrator/scripts/validate.sh --all

## Task Lifecycle

```bash
bash ../archetype-orchestrator/scripts/pre-work-check.sh
python ../archetype-orchestrator/engine/discover.py --query "task description"
# ... work on feature branch ...
bash ../archetype-orchestrator/scripts/context-checkpoint.sh "milestone"
bash ../archetype-orchestrator/scripts/post-work-check.sh
```

## Archetypes Available (../my-archetypes)

- security-guardian: security guardrails, devsecops, threat modeling
- prompt-injection-guard: prompt injection defense, LLM sanitization
- code-quality: clean code, refactoring, complexity reduction
- debug-detective: root-cause debugging, regression tests
- documentation-champion: API docs, README, ADRs, changelog
- owasp-devguide, semver

## Stack

- Python 3.11 standalone library — no frontend, no backend, no database
- Providers: Anthropic Claude, OpenAI, Ollama
- Tests: pytest (tests/unit/) — 80% coverage threshold
- Linting: ruff
- Pending: Full documentation — see docs/planning/DOCUMENTATION_IMPLEMENTATION_BRIEF.md
